headline: CME Q3 Deep Dive: Product Expansion Offsets Revenue Decline as Market Data and Crypto Lead
summary: Financial derivatives exchange CME Group (NASDAQ:CME) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales fell by 3% year on year to $1.54 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.68 per share was 2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: CME Group (CME) Margin Expansion Reinforces Bullish Narrative Despite Slower Growth Forecasts
summary: CME Group (CME) posted a net profit margin of 57.9%, up from last year’s 56.4%, as annual earnings growth reached 14.1%. This outpaced its five-year average of 12.4%. Looking ahead, analysts forecast earnings to grow 5.5% per year and revenue to climb 5% annually, both trailing the broader US market’s projections. Against this backdrop, the risk-reward profile centers on CME’s strong history of profitability and consistent growth, supported by few major identified risks. See our full analysis...
